text.tspan: Window offices of the Department of Geography
University of Kentucky central campus, Lexington, Kentucky
was spelled letter-by-letter in departmental windows facing
southwest during the departments 75th anniversary celebration.
Viz created by @boydx, April 2023, using Phase 2 lidar point cloud data
hosted by KyFromAbove.gov. An elevation profile was created for the four
aspects of the building with 50ft offsets in QGIS. The resulting vector artwork
was exported to Adobe Illustrator for final design.
